      <section name='fountain'>

         <para number='1' comment='fountain color change msg'>
         The fountain abruptly changes color to an electric neon pink.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='fountain color change msg'>
         The color of the fountain slowly changes until it is a soothing, restful, green.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='fountain color change msg'>
         Movement catches your eye and you turn and watch the fountain slowly change to a rather nice cool blue color.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='fountain color change msg'>
         The fountain changes color to a violent, alarming crimson.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='fountain color change msg'>
         The fountain changes color to a rather startling bright canary yellow.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='fountain color change msg'>
         The fountain becomes a rather tasteless muddy brown color.
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='fountain color change msg'>
         The liquid in the fountain transforms itself into a translucent, milky white, color.
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='fountain color change msg'>
         The fountain suddenly swiches to dynamic bands of color swirling around the liquid. It's quite an impressive display at the moment.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='locations'>

         <para number='1' comment='loc 1443'>
         There follows a series of harrowing 2D color pictures of executions and torture, taken from the period while humans were still confined to Earth. The move to holographs coincides with the exploration and colonizing of the planets and reaching the stars.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='loc 1443 cont'>
         This section has holos of the xenocide on Sirius V, and the use of mass-drivers against civilian populations. These pictures led directly to the formulation of the Rigel Accords declaring such acts war crimes.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='loc 1443 cont'>
         Finally there is a series of famous holos of atrocities committed by the Praetorian Guard, publication of which triggered the fall of the House of Ming. The net result of the exhibition is a sobering reminder of the sort of behavior both humans and non-humans are capable of.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='loc 1443 cont'>
         As a coda, in the south east corner, by the exit is a polished six foot high slab of Venusian fire opal with some writing carved into it.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='location 1571'>
         One of today's holos seems to be a bunch of men, wearing some sort of strange armor, running round in an endless plain of waist high grass looking for some women (who aren't wearing armor). Very odd.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='location 1571'>
         A second holo seems to have been made completely in black and white. It shows an endless series of street demonstrations, clashes with police, rioting and burning factories. Since it has no spoken soundtrack, or subtitles, it's very difficult to figure out what's going on.
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='location 1571'>
         The final holo is about some sort of existentialist party. All the guests seem to be standing against the walls, occasionally uttering cryptic remarks while holding a drink of their choice in a plastic cup. To say that the holo was opaque would be something of an understatement!
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='location 1571'>
         The overall effect of the three different holos all playing in the same space is indescribable. After watching for a while you start to develop a headache! Some people, though, are watching it all with rapt attention. Each to their own. In the mean time the exit is north east.
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='loc 2393 extra text'>
         The salesman is calling out a series of numbers, and for each number the tech produces a different background. Judging from the --Oooh's-- and the --Aaah's-- from the watchers, it's making quite an impression.
         </para>

         <para number='10' comment='loc 2393 extra text'>
         As you watch the droid calls out "42" and the tech produces a background set in the Norwegian fjords. There is an appreciative round of applause, and you take the opportunity to glance around, but there is nothing else to see except the door in the south wall.
         </para>

