      <section name='buzzer'>

         <para number='1' comment='press buzzer - msg to room'>
         A loud buzzing sound tells you someone has pressed their buzzer. A quick look at the contestants shows you that the light has come on in front of %s.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Press buzzer - player message'>
         You press your buzzer. The button lights up with a bright red light, and a loud buzzing noise fills the studio.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='Examine portable buzzer'>
         This special portable buzzer can be moved out of the studio - even to different planets - so that the game can be played on location. It's actually a whole set of buzzers mounted on a board, running off a big battery pack.
         </para>

         <para number='4'>
         Each buzzer is a large red button - one for each contestant (and somehow there are always just the right number of buzzers!) Press it, and it will light up and make a noise.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='Get buzzer - staff'>
         You pick up the board containing the buzzers and tuck it under one of your arms (or equivalent appendages).
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='Non-staff'>
         You start to pick up the buzzer board, but before you can lift it, a studio engineer bustles up and asks to see your authorization to move it. Since you don't have any, you step away from the buzzer and try to look innocent.
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='Drop buzzer'>
         You put the buzzer board down with a thud, setting it up so it is all ready to be used in an event. Each buzzer gives a little buzz to prove that they are all working.
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='Get buzzer - staff - roomex'>
         With a heave, %s picks up the board containing the buzzers and tucks it under one arm (or equivalent appendage).
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='Drop buzzer - roomex'>
         You hear a thud followed by a series of buzzes, and see that %s has set up a board with a set of buzzers mounted on it, ready to play an event.
         </para>

