      <section name='dylan'>

         <para number='1' comment='Examine Dylan (1)'>
         A creature a little like a large version of an Earth rabbit is sitting on the floor with his back to the wall. He is slumped over a guitar and appears to be fast asleep.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Examine Dylan (2)'>
         He's wearing a badge with a curious picture on it, and on the floor by his feet is an old workman's cap.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='toss coin to dylan (1)'>
         You toss a 20 groat coin into the cap, and Dylan wakes up with a start.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='toss coin to dylan (2)'>
         "Groovy man!" he says and strums a few chords on the guitar. He begins to sing, "Well, I woke up this morning..."
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='toss coin to dylan (2)'>
         At this stage he falls asleep again and slumps back over his guitar.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='shake/talk to dylan'>
         Dylan surfaces briefly, mutters, "Wassamatterman..." and goes back to sleep.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='emily'>

         <para number='1' comment='Emily chat - hello'>
         "Hello dearie", she says cheerfully. "Welcome to my emporium. Feel free to look around with no obligation, but be careful, some of the items are hot, so to speak."
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='arm I'>
         "This arm?" She grins a wicked grin and flexes the mechanical arm with a hiss of steam. "There's quite a story behind it." She then proceeds to tell you a colorful, and highly improbable, tale of an escapade.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='arm II'>
         The story weaves in Ming's illegitimate daughter, time travel, the 1st Marchioness of Salisbury (who died when her hair caught fire after being entangled in a chandelier), and a three-legged albino Rigellian snarcot.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='arm III'>
         Struggling to keep a straight face, you smile politely and nod.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='lattice'>
         "Nice place, unless you are color blind, in which case all the disks look the same color. Just as well Galactic Admin equal opportunities don't apply here!"
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='vocab - bye'>
         "Bye." She waves to you and blends back into the steamy atmosphere.
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='job'>
         She gives you a strange look. "I'm the proprieteuse of this magnificent establishment, of course!"
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='emporium'>
         Emily smiles modestly. "It's just a few bits and pieces that I picked up along the way. Mainly stuff those pompous stuffed shirts at the Galactic Administration would like to see banned as too dangerous."
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='ming'>
         "Ming? I know people didn't like him, but he had his good points you know..." Her face takes on a dreamy look, and she refuses to talk further about the subject.
         </para>

         <para number='10' comment='gaelaan'>
         "What a twit - Martians bearing gifts, indeed. What probably happened to him was that his friends the Martians caught him and drained all the blood out of him. Good riddance I say."
         </para>

         <para number='11' comment='teleporter I'>
         "Our teleporters? One hundred percent genuine navy Mk1 teleporters. You can only get them on The Lattice, because it's outside the Galactic Administration's control. They cost a slithy a month to rent, and work everywhere except that they can't cross cartel boundaries. Well... there are a couple of other restrictions, but they're not worth mentioning."
         </para>

         <para number='12' comment='teleporter II'>
         She waves her mechanical arm which emits a dismissive puff of steam.
         </para>

         <para number='13' comment='orrery'>
         "The one next door? Brilliant isn't it! It was too big to fit in here. The techs love it. They threatened to go on strike if the Protector didn't give me a room large enough to install it in."
         </para>

         <para number='14' comment='Nomatch'>
         Emily shrugs, and her arm makes a clanking noise.
         </para>

