      <section name='notice'>

         <para number='1' comment='xtra text for reception notice'>
         Visitors are permitted to make use of the public portions of the Lattice teleportation system. To use the system, 'STEP ONTO color' where 'color' is the color of the disk you wish to use. The public portions of the system are as follows:
         </para>

         <para number='2'>
         yellow - to the Lattice production complex
         </para>

         <para number='3'>
         black  - to the local offices of Armstrong Cuthbert Inc
         </para>

         <para number='4'>
         blue   - to the commodities exchange
         </para>

         <para number='5'>
         green  - to the leisure and visitor complex
         </para>

         <para number='6'>
         white  - return to the reception area
         </para>

         <para number='7'>
         You may also use grey disks which are for local sub-complexes.
         </para>

         <para number='8'>
         Visitors are prohibited from using gold disks and are warned that red disks are extremely dangerous and often lead to areas likely to be fatal to both organic and non-organic beings.
         </para>

